The paper deals with the problem of sampling signals on graphs, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several CS subfields. However, the focus on bandlimited signals and the use of coherence as a performance metric suggest that the paper is most likely to be classified under cs.IT (Information Theory). The use of random sampling and the emphasis on computational efficiency also suggest that the paper could be classified under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.LG (Machine Learning), respectively. The use of graphs as a data structure and the focus on signal processing suggest that the paper could also be classified under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
